<emphasis id="B97DE5725751FFB5FF085ADFFEBC21F8" bold="true" box="[151,267,151,177]" pageId="22" pageNumber="453">Remarks.</emphasis>
Herein we propose the transfer of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35751FFB5FD215ADFFCE321F9" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1985" box="[702,852,151,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pisac">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725751FFB5FD215ADFFCE321F9" box="[702,852,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="453">Hurius pisac</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35751FFB5FC1A5ADFFBB221F8" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1988" box="[901,1029,151,177]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725751FFB5FC1A5ADFFBB221F8" box="[901,1029,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="453">Simonurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on the morphology of the spermathecae and atrium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3136AEB5751FFB5FF585A96FB462008" pageId="22" pageNumber="453" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB639605751FFB5FF585A96FB462008" blockId="22.[151,1436,151,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="453">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725751FFB5FF585A96FEF521B1" bold="true" box="[199,322,222,248]" pageId="22" pageNumber="453">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The S 
<quantity id="4CF194855751FFB5FE0F5A97FE0D21B0" box="[400,442,223,249]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="22" pageNumber="453" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35751FFB5FE5C5A97FD3121B1" authorityName="Marta &amp; Bustamante &amp; Ruiz &amp; Teixeira &amp; Hagopián &amp; Brescovit &amp; Valiati &amp; Rodrigues" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Galiano" baseAuthorityYear="1985" box="[451,646,223,249]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pisac" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725751FFB5FE5C5A97FD3121B1" box="[451,646,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="453">Simonurius pisac</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97DE5725751FFB5FD105A97FCA621B0" bold="true" box="[655,785,223,249]" pageId="22" pageNumber="453">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24E58095751FFB5FD105A97FCA621B0" box="[655,785,223,249]" pageId="22" pageNumber="453" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is wider than S 
<quantity id="4CF194855751FFB5FC565A97FC4421B0" box="[969,1011,223,249]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="22" pageNumber="453" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35751FFB5FC645A97FBCD21B0" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[1019,1146,223,249]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladifer">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725751FFB5FC645A97FBCD21B0" box="[1019,1146,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="453">Si. gladifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with inclination close to each other (see epigyne variation of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35751FFB5FDB65B4BFD122054" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[553,677,259,285]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladifer">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725751FFB5FDB65B4BFD122054" box="[553,677,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="453">Si. gladifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and have anterior S2, above S1, long and slender. Finally, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35751FFB5FAA15B4BFA2B2055" authorityName="Marta &amp; Bustamante &amp; Ruiz &amp; Teixeira &amp; Hagopián &amp; Brescovit &amp; Valiati &amp; Rodrigues" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Galiano" baseAuthorityYear="1985" box="[1342,1436,259,285]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pisac">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725751FFB5FAA15B4BFA2B2055" box="[1342,1436,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="453">Si. pisac</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35751FFB5FEF85B6FFE502008" authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1988" box="[359,487,295,321]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Simonurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="453" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725751FFB5FEF85B6FFE502008" box="[359,487,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="453">Simonurius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by U-shape antero-medial atrium, like in other females of this genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3136AEB5751FFB5FF585B02FB97202C" box="[199,1056,330,357]" pageId="22" pageNumber="453" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB639605751FFB5FF585B02FB97202C" blockId="22.[151,1436,151,429]" box="[199,1056,330,357]" pageId="22" pageNumber="453">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725751FFB5FF585B02FEEE202D" bold="true" box="[199,345,330,356]" pageId="22" pageNumber="453">Description.</emphasis>
Female: see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9844915751FFB5FE735B03FD79202C" author="Galiano, M. E." box="[492,718,330,357]" pageId="22" pageNumber="453" pagination="9 - 18" refId="ref17368" refString="Galiano, M. E. (1985) Revision del genero Hurius Simon, 1901 (Araneae, Salticidae). Journal of Arachnology, 13, 9 - 18." type="journal article" year="1985">Galiano (1985 p. 17</bibRefCitation>
, figs 22–24). Male: unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
